Projects

Audify - An Audio Classification System using Deep Learning

Method: Developed an audio classification system, using Deep Learning techniques. Utilizing the Ur- banSound8K dataset, implemented a Deep Neural Network model with TensorFlow and Keras.

Results: This model achieved an accuracy of 83.87% in training and 78.28% in testing on a substantial audio dataset by using MFCC (Mel-Frequency Cepstral Coefficients) feature using librosa an audio pro- cessing library in Python.

Libraries used : librosa, Keras, TensorFlow, pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib

Research Paper
Github

Deep CNN - Based Detection of Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia (ALL) in Blood Cell Images

Method: Developed a Deep CNN model using Keras, TensorFlow, and Sklearn to classify benign and malignant blood cells from Peripheral Blood Smear (PBS) images.

Results: The model achieved a robust 94.1% testing accuracy, with an 86.3% training accuracy and also achieved a specificity of 95.81%, sensitivity of 95.91%, F1-score of 95.43%, and precision of 96%.

Libraries Used: Keras, TensorFlow, NumPy, pandas, Matplotlib.

Research Paper
Github
